lavet. The active of this verb is sometimes used intransitively, in the sense of the passive, or rather middle ; cs. Haut. 618, Liv. 44. 6.

post deinde. Notice the tautology, cf. 106 note: here perhaps purposely put into the mouth of an uneducated woman. Deinde is here scanned as a trisyllable.

484. dari bibere. Three constructions are used to express ‘to give to drink:’ (1) Simple infi. as here. cf. Pl. Pers. 5. 2. 40, Cic. Tusc. 1. 26. 65, Liv. 40. 47. 5. This is a Graecism. (2) Subjunctivc. cf. Pl. Stich. 757 tum vos date bibat tibicini. (3) Quod wito subj. Cf. Pl. Cist. 1. 1. 19 nimium dabat quod biberem.
